  "text": "The Envoy xDS v2 to v3 API migration is implemented through several key C++ source files in the config subscription and ADS (Aggregated Discovery Service) server infrastructure.\n\n**Primary Implementation Files:**\n\n1. **Unified xDS Mux Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/):**\n   - `grpc_mux_impl.h` and `grpc_mux_impl.cc`: Contains the template-based `GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS>` class that handles both SotW (State of the World) and Delta discovery protocols. The template parameters RQ and RS represent the request and response proto types, supporting both v2 (DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse) and v3 (DiscoveryRequest v3/DiscoveryResponse v3) types.\n   - `sotw_subscription_state.h` and `sotw_subscription_state.cc`: Manages subscription state for SotW protocol with v2/v3 compatibility.\n   - `delta_subscription_state.h` and `delta_subscription_state.cc`: Manages subscription state for Delta protocol with v2/v3 compatibility.\n   - `subscription_state.h`: Base interface for subscription state management.\n\n2. **Legacy GrpcMux Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/):**\n   - `grpc_mux_impl.h` and `grpc_mux_impl.cc`: Legacy SotW-only GrpcMux implementation using v3 discovery types (envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest/Response).\n   - `new_grpc_mux_impl.h` and `new_grpc_mux_impl.cc`: New Delta-only GrpcMux implementation using v3 discovery types (envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryRequest/Response).\n\n3. **Subscription Factory (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/):**\n   - `grpc_subscription_factory.h` and `grpc_subscription_factory.cc`: Creates subscriptions for SotW GRPC, Delta GRPC, and ADS. The factory handles API version configuration through the `transport_api_version` field in `ApiConfigSource`.\n\n4. **Failover Support:**\n   - `grpc_mux_failover.h`: Implements failover logic between primary and secondary xDS sources with v2/v3 proto type support through template parameters.\n\n5. **Resource Decoding and Management:**\n   - `source/common/config/decoded_resource_impl.h`: Handles decoded resource representation with support for versioned proto types.\n   - `source/common/config/opaque_resource_decoder_impl.h`: Resource decoder that maintains v2/v3 compatibility.\n   - `source/common/config/xds_manager_impl.h` and `xds_manager_impl.cc`: Manages multiple xDS subscriptions with v2/v3 version awareness.\n   - `source/common/config/subscription_factory_impl.h` and `subscription_factory_impl.cc`: Creates subscriptions based on ConfigSource configuration.\n\n6. **Proto Link Hacks:**\n   - `source/common/config/protobuf_link_hacks.h`: Forces linking of v3 proto definitions.\n   - `test/config/v2_link_hacks.h`: Forces linking of v2 proto definitions for testing.\n\n**Key Field Renames and Migration Patterns:**\n\nThe v2-to-v3 migration is defined in the proto files with `(udpa.annotations.field_migrate)` annotations:\n- `api/envoy/api/v2/discovery.proto`: Defines v2 DiscoveryRequest and DeltaDiscoveryRequest messages that are annotated to migrate to v3.\n- `api/envoy/api/v2/core/config_source.proto`: Defines ApiVersion enum with V2 (deprecated) and V3 values, controlling transport API version selection.\n\n**ADS gRPC Server and Dual-Version Handling:**\n\nThe ADS implementation supports both v2 and v3 through:\n1. **Runtime Feature Flags**: The unified mux uses `envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux` to select between legacy (GrpcMuxImpl, NewGrpcMuxImpl) and unified implementations (Config::XdsMux::GrpcMuxSotw, Config::XdsMux::GrpcMuxDelta).\n2. **Template-Based Protocol Handling**: The xds_mux `GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS>` template allows single codebase to handle both SotW and Delta with v2 or v3 proto types.\n3. **API Version Configuration**: The `transport_api_version` field in `ApiConfigSource` controls which protocol version is used on the wire, while `resource_api_version` controls the resource message versions.\n\n**Subscription Lifecycle:**\n\nWhen a subscription is created (in `GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory::create`), the factory determines the appropriate Mux implementation based on:\n1. The API type (GRPC for SotW, DELTA_GRPC for Delta)\n2. Whether the unified mux feature is enabled\n3. The transport_api_version setting (though v2 is now deprecated)\n\nThe subscription then uses the selected mux to send discovery requests and handle responses through the appropriate SubscriptionState implementation (SotwSubscriptionState or DeltaSubscriptionState)."
